 The incident occurred five kilometres from the Hendrina off-ramp at about 19:00 on Monday. The cattle owner told www.mobserver.co.za that the fencing around his property was stolen, hence the four cattle went astray. The Department of Community Safety, Security and Liason said that a driver and one passenger were seriously injured whilst four other people sustained slight injuries. They were transported to hospital for further medical treatment. The taxi was travelling to Mozambique when it bumped into one of the cows. Taxi commuters travelling to Mozambique said they did not notice the cows until it was too late for the taxi driver to stop the vehicle. Elize van Wyngaardt from Belfast said she was travelling home from Pretoria in her late father’s car when she crashed into one of the cows. “This is my only source of transport, I mean my father drove this car for 20 years without any mechanical problems or accidents, ” said Ms Van Wyngaardt.       Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za